1
00:00:08,041 --> 00:00:10,333
♪

2
00:00:11,791 --> 00:00:15,250
This force is something
far more terrible.

3
00:00:18,541 --> 00:00:20,000
[SOLDIERS gasp]

4
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:25,208
The fifth dimension's unfolding.

5
00:00:25,291 --> 00:00:27,666
Alongside the sixth one.

6
00:00:27,750 --> 00:00:28,708
And the seventh.

7
00:00:28,791 --> 00:00:29,750
They're all...

8
00:00:31,125 --> 00:00:32,958
[gasps]
No.

9
00:00:33,041 --> 00:00:34,583
It can't be.

10
00:00:34,666 --> 00:00:36,000
This is the end.

11
00:00:36,083 --> 00:00:37,250
We're doomed.

12
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:39,291
♪

13
00:00:43,833 --> 00:00:46,916
This is something
I never thought I'd see.

14
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:49,416
The Philosopher's Stone
will kill us all.

15
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:50,875
Wait, hold on.

16
00:00:50,958 --> 00:00:52,750
I thought you said
I was just going to die

17
00:00:52,833 --> 00:00:54,208
if it went out of control.

18
00:00:54,291 --> 00:00:55,750
What is that thing?

19
00:00:55,833 --> 00:00:57,541
♪

20
00:01:03,291 --> 00:01:06,250
[SOLDIERS coughing, groaning]

21
00:01:06,333 --> 00:01:08,000
What's happening to the sky?

22
00:01:08,083 --> 00:01:10,208
Dear God, help us.

23
00:01:11,791 --> 00:01:13,125
[LA HIRE]
Montmorency!

24
00:01:13,208 --> 00:01:14,208
What's going on?

25
00:01:14,291 --> 00:01:15,875
How is there a hole in the sky?

26
00:01:15,958 --> 00:01:17,791
And what is that
terrible monster?

27
00:01:21,125 --> 00:01:22,375
[MONTMORENCY]
La Hire,

28
00:01:22,458 --> 00:01:24,625
take Jeanne
and Astaroth and run.

29
00:01:24,708 --> 00:01:26,666
Get as far away from this place
as you can.

30
00:01:26,750 --> 00:01:28,083
[LA HIRE]
And just leave you here?

31
00:01:28,166 --> 00:01:29,375
What will you do?

32
00:01:29,458 --> 00:01:30,500
[MONTMORENCY grunts]

33
00:01:30,583 --> 00:01:33,000
♪

34
00:01:34,083 --> 00:01:35,875
[growling]

35
00:01:37,958 --> 00:01:39,125
Leave, now!

36
00:03:16,708 --> 00:03:18,458
Mur d'Air!

37
00:03:18,541 --> 00:03:20,375
♪

38
00:03:21,458 --> 00:03:23,250
[ALL groaning]

39
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:29,791
[NICOLAS]
This is it.

40
00:03:32,125 --> 00:03:33,666
[grunting]

41
00:03:37,041 --> 00:03:38,500
Be gone, foul monster!

42
00:03:41,958 --> 00:03:43,083
[grunts]

43
00:03:44,250 --> 00:03:46,416
I don't know what you are
or why you've come here,

44
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:48,541
but you are not welcome.

45
00:03:48,625 --> 00:03:50,833
Now back to the hell
from whence you came!

46
00:03:50,916 --> 00:03:52,333
[roaring]

47
00:03:56,291 --> 00:03:57,250
[grunts]

48
00:04:00,666 --> 00:04:02,125
[ALENCON]
Retreat at full speed!

49
00:04:02,208 --> 00:04:03,291
Keep moving!

50
00:04:07,458 --> 00:04:09,458
Babylon's Hole.

51
00:04:13,208 --> 00:04:14,416
[grunting]

52
00:04:24,291 --> 00:04:26,500
[screaming]

53
00:04:30,791 --> 00:04:33,500
[ASTAROTH] I never imagined
it would happen like this.

54
00:04:33,583 --> 00:04:36,958
It couldn't possibly have
manifested in a worse way.

55
00:04:37,041 --> 00:04:39,291
[MONTMORENCY groaning]

56
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,833
[screaming]

57
00:04:54,375 --> 00:04:55,750
[MONTMORENCY]
Where am I?

58
00:05:00,166 --> 00:05:02,166
What am I looking at?

59
00:05:02,250 --> 00:05:03,500
Am I dead?

60
00:05:03,583 --> 00:05:04,458
[gasps]

61
00:05:06,833 --> 00:05:09,916
♪

62
00:05:13,166 --> 00:05:14,916
I am king of the gods!

63
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,625
Lowly, insolent human.

64
00:05:16,708 --> 00:05:19,000
How dare you attempt
to seal a divine being

65
00:05:19,083 --> 00:05:20,000
in the Void Dimension?

66
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:27,291
Astaroth?

67
00:05:27,375 --> 00:05:30,166
[Z] We are the makers
who created the human race.

68
00:05:30,250 --> 00:05:33,833
What you are attempting to do
is heresy, the murder of a god!

69
00:05:33,916 --> 00:05:35,208
It is a mortal sin!

70
00:05:35,291 --> 00:05:37,541
Humans are lost
without their masters!

71
00:05:37,625 --> 00:05:38,916
Deprived of our guidance,

72
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:41,541
your race will let loose
your drives and desires!

73
00:05:41,625 --> 00:05:44,500
This can only lead
to eternal war and strife.

74
00:05:44,583 --> 00:05:47,541
We maintained the peace in
your realm by ruling over you.

75
00:05:47,625 --> 00:05:48,958
Your species has proved
time and again

76
00:05:49,041 --> 00:05:51,416
to be incapable
of surviving on your own!

77
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:53,500
As a result, you will lose
your chance

78
00:05:53,583 --> 00:05:56,708
of achieving utopia permanently!

79
00:05:56,791 --> 00:05:58,875
[groans]

80
00:05:58,958 --> 00:06:02,416
We will return, no matter
what you do to keep us away.

81
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:05,250
This I promise you!

82
00:06:05,333 --> 00:06:07,916
♪

83
00:06:17,583 --> 00:06:18,500
[gasps]

84
00:06:18,583 --> 00:06:19,958
Goodbye, friend.

85
00:06:20,041 --> 00:06:21,333
We must now part.

86
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:25,458
[ASTAROTH]
You can't die, not right now.

87
00:06:25,541 --> 00:06:27,750
Don't leave me here in a world
without gods.

88
00:06:27,833 --> 00:06:29,458
I can't make it on my own.

89
00:06:29,541 --> 00:06:31,250
Do not worry,
for not all the gods

90
00:06:31,333 --> 00:06:33,541
have vanished from this world.

91
00:06:33,625 --> 00:06:35,375
There is still a goddess here.

92
00:06:35,458 --> 00:06:39,041
It's you, for you have the power
needed to save humanity.

93
00:06:39,125 --> 00:06:40,166
Bless us.

94
00:06:41,916 --> 00:06:45,666
The future of utopia...
is with you.

95
00:06:45,750 --> 00:06:46,791
Farewell.

96
00:07:11,583 --> 00:07:13,833
[rumbling]

97
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,000
[ALL gasp]

98
00:07:17,083 --> 00:07:19,333
♪

99
00:07:25,458 --> 00:07:27,500
No. It's a demon!

100
00:07:27,583 --> 00:07:28,875
Attack!

101
00:07:28,958 --> 00:07:30,333
[arrows shooting]

102
00:07:30,416 --> 00:07:32,125
♪

103
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:41,833
[SOLDIERS clamoring]

104
00:07:41,916 --> 00:07:44,250
[distorted voice]
I've obtained it at last.

105
00:07:44,333 --> 00:07:47,166
The Philosopher's Stone
that once sealed me away.

106
00:07:47,250 --> 00:07:48,666
It's within my grasp!

107
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:50,333
[yelling]

108
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,875
There's nothing for me
to fear now.

109
00:07:56,958 --> 00:07:58,458
[evil laughter]

110
00:07:58,541 --> 00:07:59,958
Vessel in the heavens.

111
00:08:00,041 --> 00:08:01,458
Hasten to my voice.

112
00:08:01,541 --> 00:08:04,250
♪

113
00:08:31,333 --> 00:08:32,916
[screaming]

114
00:08:42,833 --> 00:08:45,791
[MONTMORENCY] The Hole
of Babylon has opened at last,

115
00:08:45,875 --> 00:08:48,041
and it is under my control.

116
00:08:48,125 --> 00:08:49,625
We shall have our utopia,

117
00:08:49,708 --> 00:08:52,000
that idyllic realm
shall begin once more.

118
00:08:52,083 --> 00:08:53,416
But before that,

119
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:56,833
I must cleanse it
of the filthy human scourge.

120
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:05,458
[NICOLAS] It is coming to pass
precisely as foretold.

121
00:09:05,541 --> 00:09:06,708
[ASTAROTH]
It's you.

122
00:09:06,791 --> 00:09:08,125
[NICOLAS]
I should have acted that day,

123
00:09:08,208 --> 00:09:11,666
and taken his life
when I had the opportunity.

124
00:09:11,750 --> 00:09:14,666
But no,
I still wanted to believe.

125
00:09:14,750 --> 00:09:17,791
I held out hope that people
weren't slaves to fate.

126
00:09:17,875 --> 00:09:20,666
I thought love had the power
to alter his destiny.

127
00:09:20,750 --> 00:09:23,208
Could you at least talk
like a normal person?!

128
00:09:23,291 --> 00:09:25,166
What in the hell just happened
to Montmorency?

129
00:09:25,250 --> 00:09:28,041
What was that horrible monster
that came out of the sky?

130
00:09:28,125 --> 00:09:29,958
And what is going on right now?

131
00:09:31,666 --> 00:09:32,625
[grunts in frustration]

132
00:09:32,708 --> 00:09:34,083
Fine then, keep your secrets,

133
00:09:34,166 --> 00:09:35,791
but tell us what to do,
at least.

134
00:09:35,875 --> 00:09:37,208
How can we stop this?

135
00:09:37,291 --> 00:09:38,583
Nothing can be done.

136
00:09:38,666 --> 00:09:39,916
[gasps]

137
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,000
He is our only remaining hope.

138
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:45,291
"Only hope"? Who are you?

139
00:09:45,375 --> 00:09:47,791
I am Nicolas Flamel.

140
00:09:47,875 --> 00:09:49,916
And I am here
as a representative

141
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,250
of an organization

142
00:09:51,333 --> 00:09:53,875
formed to establish
a utopia for humanity,

143
00:09:53,958 --> 00:09:56,208
called the Knights Templar.

144
00:09:56,291 --> 00:09:58,375
I am its last surviving member.

145
00:10:01,666 --> 00:10:04,875
Now, Astaroth,
you cannot escape.

146
00:10:04,958 --> 00:10:06,500
At long last,
I have come to kill you.

147
00:10:06,583 --> 00:10:07,541
[gasps]

148
00:10:09,041 --> 00:10:11,250
Hurry up!
Get to the fortress, quickly!

149
00:10:11,333 --> 00:10:12,166
[BATARD]
Right.

150
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:16,041
[explosion]

151
00:10:17,041 --> 00:10:18,666
[LA HIRE]
Will Astaroth be all right?

152
00:10:18,750 --> 00:10:19,791
I don't like leaving her.

153
00:10:19,875 --> 00:10:21,291
[ALENCON]
We don't have any choice.

154
00:10:21,375 --> 00:10:23,000
We must get to
Augustine Fortress

155
00:10:23,083 --> 00:10:24,208
as soon as possible.

156
00:10:24,291 --> 00:10:25,875
[BATARD]
Even if we hide in the fortress,

157
00:10:25,958 --> 00:10:27,625
it will probably meet
the same awful end

158
00:10:27,708 --> 00:10:29,250
as the Tourelles Complex.

159
00:10:29,333 --> 00:10:30,750
[whimpers]

160
00:10:30,833 --> 00:10:32,291
I had hoped I'd be able to die
looking like a boy,

161
00:10:32,375 --> 00:10:34,250
or at the very least,
that I wouldn't have to perish

162
00:10:34,333 --> 00:10:35,875
wearing frilly
women's underwear.

163
00:10:35,958 --> 00:10:37,750
Please, Lord,
let me go to heaven

164
00:10:37,833 --> 00:10:39,458
where I may dress as I wish.

165
00:10:39,541 --> 00:10:41,333
You can't be serious right now.

166
00:10:41,416 --> 00:10:42,833
Don't pray to God.

167
00:10:42,916 --> 00:10:45,250
We must defeat divinity
to survive.

168
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:53,333
[NICOLAS]
We, of the Knights Templar,

169
00:10:53,416 --> 00:10:55,000
fought our way toward the east

170
00:10:55,083 --> 00:10:57,708
with a single,
particular goal in our hearts.

171
00:10:57,791 --> 00:10:59,583
We wanted nothing more than
to destroy

172
00:10:59,666 --> 00:11:02,625
every Philosopher's Stone
that lie hidden there.

173
00:11:02,708 --> 00:11:04,458
But then, a traitor among us

174
00:11:04,541 --> 00:11:07,000
smuggled one of the Stones
back into France,

175
00:11:07,083 --> 00:11:09,958
and it somehow ended up
in Montmorency's hands.

176
00:11:12,208 --> 00:11:13,291
[grunts]

177
00:11:13,375 --> 00:11:15,125
[gasps]

178
00:11:15,208 --> 00:11:18,166
♪

179
00:11:21,375 --> 00:11:24,458
[MONTMORENCY]
Astaroth, you are a sinner.

180
00:11:24,541 --> 00:11:25,916
I have been dreaming of the day

181
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:29,083
I'd exact my revenge
for thousands of years.

182
00:11:30,458 --> 00:11:31,958
[NICOLAS]
Now that I think of it,

183
00:11:32,041 --> 00:11:35,333
perhaps this was our destiny,
a curse upon humankind.

184
00:11:35,416 --> 00:11:37,458
For it was inevitable
that the gods would wish

185
00:11:37,541 --> 00:11:39,583
to take their world back,
no matter what the cost.

186
00:11:39,666 --> 00:11:41,666
[MONTMORENCY]
You're in my way, human.

187
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:43,166
Stand aside, or else--

188
00:11:43,250 --> 00:11:44,083
I refuse.

189
00:11:44,166 --> 00:11:45,625
Oh, do you?

190
00:11:45,708 --> 00:11:48,083
[NICOLAS]
This is the realm of humanity.

191
00:11:54,458 --> 00:11:57,833
Now, gods, bear witness
to human magic.

192
00:11:57,916 --> 00:12:01,750
Behold, a technique developed
solely by humanity.

193
00:12:01,833 --> 00:12:03,041
We call it Alchemy.

194
00:12:03,125 --> 00:12:04,541
[groans]

195
00:12:04,625 --> 00:12:06,958
[NICOLAS]
This world has no need of you.

196
00:12:07,041 --> 00:12:09,041
No gods,
nor Philosopher's Stones.

197
00:12:09,125 --> 00:12:10,500
Be gone.

198
00:12:10,583 --> 00:12:12,416
We will build our own utopia.

199
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:15,708
The human race shall create
it alone, with our own hands!

200
00:12:19,791 --> 00:12:22,708
These attacks are nothing
but cheap theatrics.

201
00:12:22,791 --> 00:12:24,083
[screams]

202
00:12:24,166 --> 00:12:25,708
[grunts]

203
00:12:27,750 --> 00:12:29,041
[MONTMORENCY grunts]

204
00:12:29,125 --> 00:12:31,041
[NICOLAS groans]

205
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:34,083
I gave you a command,
now move aside!

206
00:12:35,458 --> 00:12:36,791
[groans]

207
00:12:46,166 --> 00:12:48,875
A utopia crafted
by mortal hands?

208
00:12:48,958 --> 00:12:50,250
It's laughable.

209
00:12:50,333 --> 00:12:53,083
Well, Astaroth,
didn't I warn you?

210
00:12:53,166 --> 00:12:55,500
Humanity is lost
without its masters

211
00:12:55,583 --> 00:12:58,208
and will give in
to base desires and ambitions

212
00:12:58,291 --> 00:12:59,541
with reckless abandon

213
00:12:59,625 --> 00:13:02,416
resulting in endless war
and discord.

214
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:06,916
You will lose your utopia,
with no hope of recovering it.

215
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:09,333
You must admit, I was right.

216
00:13:09,416 --> 00:13:12,000
I am the guardian
of the Philosopher's Stone.

217
00:13:12,083 --> 00:13:14,416
Therefore, you cannot kill me.

218
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:16,875
[MONTMORENCY]
Oh, but I can, my darling.

219
00:13:16,958 --> 00:13:21,625
And I will continue killing you,
until the end of everything.

220
00:13:31,166 --> 00:13:33,500
It's quieted down.

221
00:13:33,583 --> 00:13:35,583
Let's go!

222
00:13:35,666 --> 00:13:38,833
[yelling]

223
00:13:38,916 --> 00:13:41,541
Take care of Jeanne for me.

224
00:13:41,625 --> 00:13:43,208
Don't do it.

225
00:13:43,291 --> 00:13:44,708
You've no elixir.

226
00:13:44,791 --> 00:13:46,166
You know what will happen.

227
00:13:46,250 --> 00:13:47,750
If you use
the Philosopher's Stone

228
00:13:47,833 --> 00:13:49,541
without it, you will die.

229
00:13:49,625 --> 00:13:51,458
If I restore
Montmorency's sanity

230
00:13:51,541 --> 00:13:53,500
before the poison spreads,
and get elixir--

231
00:13:53,583 --> 00:13:55,083
That's impossible.

232
00:13:55,166 --> 00:13:57,166
Please, give me Joyeuse.

233
00:13:57,250 --> 00:13:58,791
I'll become Ulysses.

234
00:13:59,958 --> 00:14:01,333
[LA HIRE]
Hold on, Jeanne.

235
00:14:01,416 --> 00:14:03,333
I'll get Montmorency back.

236
00:14:03,416 --> 00:14:07,000
I will save you,
even if I die doing it.

237
00:14:07,083 --> 00:14:08,625
[screams]

238
00:14:08,708 --> 00:14:10,333
[gasps]

239
00:14:10,416 --> 00:14:12,791
[screaming]

240
00:14:14,625 --> 00:14:15,791
Montmorency, please!

241
00:14:15,875 --> 00:14:17,458
I know you're in there!

242
00:14:17,541 --> 00:14:20,125
[screaming]

243
00:14:22,250 --> 00:14:24,083
[groans, sighs]

244
00:14:29,166 --> 00:14:30,041
[screams]

245
00:14:30,125 --> 00:14:32,791
[evil laughter]

246
00:14:32,875 --> 00:14:35,208
[screaming]

247
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:37,166
[LA HIRE]
That's enough! Put her down!

248
00:14:37,250 --> 00:14:38,708
[MONTMORENCY]
Huh?

249
00:14:38,791 --> 00:14:40,458
La Hire. What are you...

250
00:14:41,666 --> 00:14:43,041
[LA HIRE]
Tell me, Astaroth.

251
00:14:44,041 --> 00:14:46,541
How can I bring Montmorency
back to us?

252
00:14:46,625 --> 00:14:48,250
I'll do anything.

253
00:14:48,333 --> 00:14:49,791
[ASTAROTH]
There's only one way.

254
00:14:49,875 --> 00:14:52,083
You have to take the
Philosopher's Stone out of him.

255
00:14:52,166 --> 00:14:54,708
If you do that,
the Hole of Babylon will close,

256
00:14:54,791 --> 00:14:56,333
and the gods
will be sealed away

257
00:14:56,416 --> 00:14:58,666
back where they came from,
in the Void Dimension.

258
00:14:58,750 --> 00:15:01,166
[MONTMORENCY] You really think
that's possible?

259
00:15:02,875 --> 00:15:04,125
[LA HIRE gasps]

260
00:15:04,208 --> 00:15:06,250
You're nothing but livestock!

261
00:15:08,375 --> 00:15:09,208
[grunts]

262
00:15:09,291 --> 00:15:10,666
♪

263
00:15:14,416 --> 00:15:16,125
What is this strange weapon?

264
00:15:19,625 --> 00:15:21,000
Such speed.

265
00:15:21,083 --> 00:15:23,375
Not only that, but I can't
determine its course.

266
00:15:23,458 --> 00:15:24,708
Enchanted bullets?

267
00:15:24,791 --> 00:15:26,375
What magic is this?

268
00:15:26,458 --> 00:15:28,375
[LA HIRE]
What a rotten world we live in.

269
00:15:28,458 --> 00:15:30,333
One filled to the brim with war,

270
00:15:30,416 --> 00:15:32,208
murder and betrayal
at every turn.

271
00:15:32,291 --> 00:15:36,125
And yet, one girl chooses to
live with honesty and integrity

272
00:15:36,208 --> 00:15:37,458
in the face of such horrors.

273
00:15:37,541 --> 00:15:39,083
I refuse to let her down

274
00:15:39,166 --> 00:15:41,250
by not giving all that I have
to protect her!

275
00:15:41,333 --> 00:15:43,666
[evil laughter]

276
00:15:46,208 --> 00:15:48,166
[MONTMORENCY]
You may shoot a magical gun,

277
00:15:48,250 --> 00:15:50,208
but you cannot possibly
hit my lances,

278
00:15:50,291 --> 00:15:51,833
fashioned from hardened air.

279
00:15:51,916 --> 00:15:55,208
I'll smite you
with my Invisible Spears.

280
00:15:55,291 --> 00:15:56,916
First I will impale you,

281
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:59,583
then bite your head off
as you writhe in pain.

282
00:15:59,666 --> 00:16:01,708
Now die, human.

283
00:16:03,541 --> 00:16:05,875
Damn it!

284
00:16:05,958 --> 00:16:07,125
[gunfire]

285
00:16:07,208 --> 00:16:09,333
[screaming]

286
00:16:11,041 --> 00:16:12,666
[LA HIRE grunting]

287
00:16:16,333 --> 00:16:17,625
You're incredible, La Hire.

288
00:16:17,708 --> 00:16:18,958
Perhaps you'll beat him.

289
00:16:19,041 --> 00:16:20,458
[MONTMORENCY]
What is this?

290
00:16:20,541 --> 00:16:22,083
[laughs]

291
00:16:22,166 --> 00:16:24,333
It would appear that the Joyeuse
imbues its user

292
00:16:24,416 --> 00:16:27,458
with the skill of
virtually infallible accuracy.

293
00:16:27,541 --> 00:16:29,875
Whether or not
I can see the target,

294
00:16:29,958 --> 00:16:31,333
it's impossible to miss!

295
00:16:31,416 --> 00:16:32,250
[gunshot]

296
00:16:34,416 --> 00:16:35,708
[gasps]

297
00:16:35,791 --> 00:16:37,583
[LA HIRE groans]

298
00:16:37,666 --> 00:16:39,666
Have I reached
the time limit already?

299
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:41,291
[panting]

300
00:16:45,666 --> 00:16:47,500
[JEANNE] Though it was
only for a short while,

301
00:16:47,583 --> 00:16:49,416
I am grateful
for your protection.

302
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:52,166
Please take this.

303
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,916
No, not yet!
[grunts]

304
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:57,541
♪

305
00:17:04,166 --> 00:17:06,250
[panting]

306
00:17:07,458 --> 00:17:11,083
You're no god.
You're just a giant pain.

307
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:14,958
Oh, God.

308
00:17:19,291 --> 00:17:20,625
How can this be?

309
00:17:21,708 --> 00:17:23,375
[groaning]

310
00:17:34,250 --> 00:17:36,083
[in normal voice]
I'm sorry you got involved.

311
00:17:36,166 --> 00:17:38,958
Forgive me, La Hire.

312
00:17:39,041 --> 00:17:40,541
[breathes shakily]

313
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:51,375
[LA HIRE groans]
Montmorency.

314
00:17:52,541 --> 00:17:55,416
[MONTMORENCY] I beg you,
please kill me and let it end.

315
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:59,125
You have to shoot me in the head
and finish this.

316
00:17:59,208 --> 00:18:01,458
These awful gods have no place
in the world of humanity,

317
00:18:01,541 --> 00:18:03,250
so seal them away.

318
00:18:03,333 --> 00:18:04,583
[groaning]

319
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:07,250
Hurry, I can't hold him back
much longer!

320
00:18:07,333 --> 00:18:09,125
I'm begging you to kill me!

321
00:18:09,208 --> 00:18:10,916
[LA HIRE]
I can't do that.

322
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,333
[MONTMORENCY]
You have to.

323
00:18:12,416 --> 00:18:14,458
It's the price we must pay
for Jeanne's future,

324
00:18:14,541 --> 00:18:16,375
for the future of our world.

325
00:18:16,458 --> 00:18:19,458
My life's a trifle
compared to that.

326
00:18:19,541 --> 00:18:21,500
[LA HIRE panting]

327
00:18:25,333 --> 00:18:26,333
[gasps]

328
00:18:26,416 --> 00:18:29,250
♪

329
00:18:29,333 --> 00:18:30,500
[grunts]

330
00:18:32,958 --> 00:18:35,416
[ASTAROTH]
Montmorency, keep fighting!

331
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:36,791
Come back to us!

332
00:18:39,125 --> 00:18:40,166
[in normal voice]
Do it now.

333
00:18:41,416 --> 00:18:43,500
Someone please make it stop!

334
00:18:43,583 --> 00:18:45,000
Let me die and save the world.

335
00:18:45,083 --> 00:18:48,333
I beg you to kill me!

336
00:18:49,875 --> 00:18:50,708
[grunts]

337
00:18:53,083 --> 00:18:55,083
[gasps]
What fresh hell is this?!

338
00:18:57,208 --> 00:19:00,166
I didn't think you could become
Ulysses twice in the same day.

339
00:19:00,250 --> 00:19:01,791
Isn't that breaking the rules?

340
00:19:01,875 --> 00:19:04,375
That's true, or so I thought.

341
00:19:04,458 --> 00:19:05,625
Is that a problem?

342
00:19:05,708 --> 00:19:07,541
[grunting]

343
00:19:11,625 --> 00:19:13,166
Montmorency.

344
00:19:13,250 --> 00:19:15,458
Don't give up yet!

345
00:19:15,541 --> 00:19:19,500
I'm coming for you!

346
00:19:19,583 --> 00:19:21,541
[grunts]

347
00:19:21,625 --> 00:19:23,250
[groans]

348
00:19:23,333 --> 00:19:24,916
[gasps]

349
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:27,291
[JEANNE breathing heavily]

350
00:19:29,041 --> 00:19:30,500
[JEANNE]
You beg for death?

351
00:19:30,583 --> 00:19:32,583
Don't you dare
even think such a thing.

352
00:19:32,666 --> 00:19:34,458
How could you be such a fool?

353
00:19:34,541 --> 00:19:36,708
You promised to always
protect me.

354
00:19:36,791 --> 00:19:38,958
You swore it, remember?

355
00:19:39,041 --> 00:19:40,750
You vowed
never to leave me alone.

356
00:19:40,833 --> 00:19:43,916
To stay by my side
until the moment of my death.

357
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,375
Have you forgotten?

358
00:19:46,541 --> 00:19:47,875
Well, then, be ready.

359
00:19:47,958 --> 00:19:50,916
Because I'm about to beat
the sense back into you!

360
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:52,958
[distorted voice]
That's enough babbling, human.

361
00:19:53,041 --> 00:19:54,791
[grunts]

362
00:19:54,875 --> 00:19:57,375
I have no business with you,
foul demon,

363
00:19:57,458 --> 00:19:59,333
so you had better
stay out of my way!

364
00:19:59,416 --> 00:20:00,458
[grunts]

365
00:20:02,708 --> 00:20:05,333
[MONTMORENCY]
How dare you insult your god?

366
00:20:05,416 --> 00:20:07,916
You will pay a heavy penance
for that!

367
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,750
♪

368
00:20:12,291 --> 00:20:14,583
[blows landing]

369
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:18,458
Montmorency, look into my eyes!

370
00:20:18,541 --> 00:20:19,833
I know you're in there.

371
00:20:19,916 --> 00:20:22,291
[in normal voice]
You're here? Jeanne.

372
00:20:22,375 --> 00:20:24,000
[gasps]

373
00:20:24,083 --> 00:20:27,083
[distorted voice]
No. I won't let this happen!

374
00:20:29,708 --> 00:20:31,458
[CROWD murmuring]

375
00:20:42,708 --> 00:20:46,166
[MAN] I hereby declare,
justice has been served.

376
00:20:46,250 --> 00:20:48,125
She made a false claim
of sainthood

377
00:20:48,208 --> 00:20:49,833
and lied about her purity.

378
00:20:49,916 --> 00:20:51,416
But it's over.

379
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:54,166
She who would have plunged
France into eternal darkness

380
00:20:54,250 --> 00:20:55,541
has perished at last.

381
00:20:55,625 --> 00:20:57,166
[MONTMORENCY gasps]

382
00:20:58,333 --> 00:21:00,166
[MAN] Let it be known
throughout the land.

383
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:03,083
The foul witch shall plague
us no longer.

384
00:21:06,250 --> 00:21:08,083
[shudders]

385
00:21:09,958 --> 00:21:13,541
[MONTMORENCY screaming]

386
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:20,416
[MONTMORENCY in normal voice]
How disturbing.

387
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:22,250
What a horrific nightmare.

388
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:26,541
But it's only a dream, right?

389
00:21:26,625 --> 00:21:29,083
This can't possibly
come to pass.

390
00:21:29,166 --> 00:21:31,750
So, then, what is this
heavy feeling

391
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:33,791
in the pit of my stomach?

392
00:21:33,875 --> 00:21:37,083
This dreadful intuition that
what I glimpsed is the future.

393
00:21:37,166 --> 00:21:40,041
Is this the wretched fate
that awaits Jeanne?

394
00:21:40,125 --> 00:21:42,333
Is this her destiny,
no matter what I do?

395
00:21:42,416 --> 00:21:43,375
[sobs]

396
00:21:45,125 --> 00:21:46,250
[JEANNE]
Montmorency?

397
00:21:52,625 --> 00:21:53,958
[evil laughter]

398
00:23:27,833 --> 00:23:29,583
[NARRATOR] Montmorency's heart
is so full of darkness

399
00:23:29,666 --> 00:23:31,041
that Jeanne's voice
cannot reach him,

400
00:23:31,125 --> 00:23:32,708
and the powerful gods
descend from the void.

401
00:23:32,791 --> 00:23:34,625
I've always been fond of
the saying, "Bigger is better,"

402
00:23:34,708 --> 00:23:36,000
but I think
this is a little much.

403
00:23:36,083 --> 00:23:38,000
Episode Eleven,
"Utopia, Then."

404
00:23:38,083 --> 00:23:39,791
Sorry, folks, but this is
probably not the best time

405
00:23:39,875 --> 00:23:41,375
to start talking about boobs!

406
00:23:43,833 --> 00:23:45,083
[WOMAN]
Quel monde de merde.

